item.title: [HIVE-20617] Fix type of constants in IN expressions to have correct type
item.description: In statements like struct(a,b) IN (const struct('x','y'), ... ) the comparision in UDFIn may fail because if a or b is of char/varchar type the constants will retain string type - especially after PointlookupOptimizer compaction.
item.summary: Fix type of constants in IN expressions to have correct type
